The paper focuses on the use of deep convolutional neural networks for autonomous driving, which is a topic that falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of recurrent neural networks and optimization techniques, which are relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of low parameter counts, which is relevant to neural network compression and optimization (cs.NE).
